dict.string: Open URLs in @url() tags like this: @url(http://google.com)
A personal assistant for web developers

source bash_functions echo '{query}' > ~/to-menu-handler.txt
if [[ '{query}' == "sh"* ]]; then {query} elif [[ '{query}' == ",p"* ]]; then osascript -e ' tell application "Alfred 2" to search "{query}" #delay .2 tell application "System Events" keystroke return end tell' elif [[ '{query}' == "/"* ]]; then
# custom work for working around complicated project if [[ '{query}' == *"/theme-copies/"* ]]; then open "$(echo '{query}' | sed "s,^.*theme-copies,$HOME/active-project/theme__on_server,")" elif [[ '{query}' == *"/module-copies/"* ]]; then open "$(echo "{query}" | sed "s,^.*module-copies,$HOME/active-project/modules__on_server,")" # end custom work else
if [[ '{query}' == *"/snippets/"* ]]; then sh snippets-handler.sh '{query}' exit fi
# the majority of all passed into this script, not just links, end up here: simply being opened open '{query}'
fi # just in case it's a relative link, open it too elif [[ '{query}' == "~"* ]]; then open '{query}' # else # echo '{query}' fi
Find Assets in Active Project (Comps, Wireframes, etc)
Show SASS/LESS files in Active Project's Theme
Launch Custom Shell Scripts from "scripts" folder.
source bash_functions if [[ "{query}" == *".sh" ]]; then sh "{query}" elif [[ "{query}" == *".applescript" ]]; then osascript "{query}" fi
By placing them in this folder

on alfred_script(q) set defaultPOSIXPath to do shell script "echo $HOME/active-project/_files/scripts" set defaultPath to POSIX file defaultPOSIXPath as alias
tell me activate set resultFile to (choose file name with prompt "Save As File" default name "script.sh" default location defaultPath) end tell set referenceNumber to open for access resultFile with write permission
close access referenceNumber tell application "Finder" to open resultFile end alfred_script
Update the Alfred Project Helper. Settings will be migrated.
Open files, folders, and URLs that have been set.
Set stuff to open at start

echo "open \"{query}\"" >> ~/active-project/_files/settings/open-at-start.sh terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -subtitle "will open now" -message "Click to view current list to open" -execute "open ~/active-project/_files/settings/open-at-start.sh"
Type ",p snippets" to search and copy it
These can be easily copied later with `,p snippets`

on alfred_script(q) set defaultPOSIXPath to do shell script "echo $HOME/active-project/_files/snippets" set defaultPath to POSIX file defaultPOSIXPath as alias
tell me activate set response to the text returned of (display dialog "What is the snippet?" with title "Add Snippet" default answer return & return & return & return) set resultFile to (choose file name with prompt "Save As File" default name "My Snippet.txt" default location defaultPath) end tell set referenceNumber to open for access resultFile with write permission
write response to referenceNumber
close access referenceNumber end alfred_script

source bash_functions replacefolder site_root "{query}" rm -rf ~/active-project/site_root ln -s "{query}" ~/active-project/site_root
source bash_functions replacefolder theme "{query}" rm -rf ~/active-project/theme ln -s "{query}" ~/active-project/theme
source bash_functions replacefolder gdocs "{query}" rm -rf ~/active-project/gdocs ln -s "{query}" ~/active-project/gdocs

Can later be found by running `,p people`
Can be searched for with ',p links'

on alfred_script(q) set defaultPOSIXPath to do shell script "echo $HOME/active-project/_files/links" set defaultPath to POSIX file defaultPOSIXPath as alias tell me activate set theURL to the text returned of (display dialog "What is the URL?" with title "Add URL" default answer "http://google.com") set resultFile to (choose file name with prompt "Save As File" default name "Name of Link" default location defaultPath) as text
set text item delimiters to ":"
set fileName to last text item of resultFile set filePath to text 1 thru lastpos(resultFile, ":") of resultFile
end tell tell application "Finder" make new internet location file at filePath to theURL with properties {name:fileName} end tell end alfred_script on lastpos(textstring, thischar) return (length of textstring) - (offset of thischar in (reverse of text items of textstring as string)) end lastpos

on alfred_script(q) set defaultPOSIXPath to do shell script "echo $HOME/active-project/_files/notes" set defaultPath to POSIX file defaultPOSIXPath as alias
tell me activate set resultFile to (choose file name with prompt "Save As File" default name "note.md" default location defaultPath) end tell set referenceNumber to open for access resultFile with write permission
close access referenceNumber tell application "Finder" to open resultFile end alfred_script

source ~/.bash_functions osascript -e 'set response to the text returned of (display dialog "What do you want to append to this file?" with title "Append This" default answer return) response' >> {query} query="{query}" terminal-notifier -subtitle "Click to Open File" -title "File Appended To" -message "$(basename $query)" -execute "open {query}"

source bash_functions todos="$(getsetting todos)" echo "- {query}" >> "$todos" sh todo__done-appender.sh "$todos" /opt/local/bin/terminal-notifier -title "Todo added to bottom" -message "{query}"
if [[ "$(getsetting todos__show_list_after_task_action)" != "FALSE" ]]; then osascript -e 'tell application "Alfred 2" to search ",p todo"' fi
on alfred_script(q) tell me activate set response to the text returned of (display dialog "Add Task" with title "Task" default answer "Task") response end tell end alfred_script
on alfred_script(q) tell me activate set response to the text returned of (display dialog "Add Task" with title "Task" default answer "Task") response end tell end alfred_script

source bash_functions todos=$(getsetting todos) cat $todos > /tmp/todo.txt && echo "- {query}" > $todos && cat /tmp/todo.txt >> $todos /opt/local/bin/terminal-notifier -title "Todo added to top" -message "{query}"
if [[ "$(getsetting todos__show_list_after_task_action)" != "FALSE" ]]; then osascript -e 'tell application "Alfred 2" to search ",p todo"' fi
url_tag="$(echo "{query}" | egrep -o '@url(\S*)')" url=$(echo ${url_tag%\)} | sed "s/^@url(//") if [[ "$url" ]]; then open $url else echo "No URL found" fi
# show the next task in large type source bash_functions egrep -v "@done" $(getsetting todos) | head -1
You can now access these with ',p todo'

source bash_functions browser="$(getsetting dev_browser)" if [[ "$browser" == *"Google Chrome.app" ]]; then osascript -e 'tell application "Google Chrome" reload active tab of window 1 end tell' /opt/local/bin/terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -message "Google Chrome Refreshed" elif [[ "$browser" == *"Google Chrome Canary"* ]]; then osascript -e 'tell application "Google Chrome Canary" reload active tab of window 1 end tell' /opt/local/bin/terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -message "Google Chrome Canary Refreshed" else /opt/local/bin/terminal-notifier -title "No Browser Refreshed" -subtitle "Chrome and Chrome Canary only" -message "Perhaps no Dev Browser was set?" fi
